# Build the joelclaw-gateway plugin

## Step

Harden the prototype seed at `prototypes/agent-comms-gateway/claude-plugin/` into the production `joelclaw-gateway` Claude Code plugin (ADR-0249 §7). The seed is the starting point, not a reference — prompts (identity, vocabulary, judgment), the replay contract, and the receipt shapes with every-input-exactly-once validation harden in place. The judgment spine stands as approved: "use the smallest interruption that preserves truth."

1. Swap the throwaway journal-spool adapter for the real `readSince` from the stream seams. Delete the replay-only review renderer.
2. MCP tool families: stream (with ADR §5 receipt appends), herdr, wake (revive + aggregate-deadline timer).
3. `SessionStart` hook implementing the boot sequence: prompt files → latest `gateway.handoff` note (advisory, replay wins) → mechanical replay from the gateway's own cursor → fresh herdr snapshot. Crash path is the same minus the note.
4. `PostCompact` hook appending the silent-backstop receipt (telemetry, never a page).
5. The retire path is loop-owned, no hook. No policy in any herdr plugin; prose files are the only steering surface.

Resolved when a session with the plugin boots clean against the real stream in replay-only rehearsal and every receipt it writes validates against the seam shapes.

## Result (2026-07-21)

Hardened the prototype seed in place into the production `joelclaw-gateway` Claude Code plugin.

- Replaced the journal-spool adapter with the public `@joelclaw/message-event-log` client. The plugin now uses canonical `readSince`, the named `gateway/agent` cursor, typed appends, semantic decision keys, and append readback.
- Enforced the no-silent-cursor rule. `stream_advance_after_decision` refuses to advance unless exactly one read-back `gateway.decision.recorded` event covers the external input. Gateway-owned output has a separate mechanical skip tool so the loop does not judge its own receipts.
- Added the production MCP families: seven stream tools, four Herdr tools, and four wake tools. Wake supports durable REVIVE plus aggregate-deadline scheduling through the existing wake registry.
- Added `SessionStart`: prompt files → latest advisory `gateway.handoff` → authoritative pending replay → fresh Herdr snapshot. A real-stream rehearsal booted clean with two pending events and 34,858 characters of injected context; it performed no stream mutation.
- Added `PostCompact`: emits the silent `gateway.compaction.recorded` OTEL receipt and never pages. Live readback found event `c9762d62-e187-4300-bacd-9b7641aedfae` in ClickHouse.
- Kept retirement loop-owned in `agents/joelclaw-gateway.md`. No hook or Herdr plugin contains judgment policy.
- Deleted the prototype-only journal adapter, Pi replay runner, replay core, and review renderer.

Validation receipts:

- `bun test`: 7 pass, 0 fail.
- `pnpm biome check prototypes/agent-comms-gateway/claude-plugin`: pass, 14 files checked.
- `claude plugin validate prototypes/agent-comms-gateway/claude-plugin`: pass.
- MCP stdio initialize + `tools/list`: pass, 15 tools.
- Real `SessionStart` hook against local Convex and Herdr: pass; ordering markers present and two canonical pending events loaded.
- Real `PostCompact` hook + `joelclaw otel search gateway.compaction.recorded --hours 1`: pass.

